title.narrative: CHILD-SENSITIVE SOCIAL PROTECTION SERVIC

description.narrative: New Element, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Access To Inclusive Social Protection (Covid), Economic And Social Policy General, Public Finance And Local Governance, Reducing Child Poverty, Social Protection And Child Poverty. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Vulnerable groups, in particular children and women, benefit from improved social protection systems guided by generated evidence.

title.narrative: New Element

description.narrative: UNICEF focused efforts instrengthening the NCSP for effective implementation of the national social protection strategy. UNICEF provided technical support to the Directorate of Social Protection (NCSP Secretariat) to develop an adequate governance structure for coordination and operationalization of the system, allowing social services to reach the most vulnerable after COVID-19 second and third wave. UNICEF fostered strong partnerships with WB and civil society to leverage results in the social protection area, considering the limited financial and technical resources available at the national level. UNICEF through the Parental Education Programme capacitated and equipped all 60 social workers of DPSSF. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
